statements.sql: select column_name as `column_name` from information_schema.columns where table_schema = 'eas_fast' and table_name = 'permissions'

select `permissions`.*, `model_has_permissions`.`model_id` as `pivot_model_id`, `model_has_permissions`.`permission_id` as `pivot_permission_id`, `model_has_permissions`.`model_type` as `pivot_model_type` from `permissions` inner join `model_has_permissions` on `permissions`.`id` = `model_has_permissions`.`permission_id` where `model_has_permissions`.`model_id` = 1 and `model_has_permissions`.`model_type` = 'App\Models\User'
select column_name as `column_name` from information_schema.columns where table_schema = 'eas_fast' and table_name = 'roles'

select `roles`.*, `model_has_roles`.`model_id` as `pivot_model_id`, `model_has_roles`.`role_id` as `pivot_role_id`, `model_has_roles`.`model_type` as `pivot_model_type` from `roles` inner join `model_has_roles` on `roles`.`id` = `model_has_roles`.`role_id` where `model_has_roles`.`model_id` = 1 and `model_has_roles`.`model_type` = 'App\Models\User'
select count(*) as aggregate from `markets` where `id` = '1'
select count(*) as aggregate from `categories` where `id` = '1'

select `value`, `view`, `name` from `custom_field_values` inner join `custom_fields` on `custom_fields`.`id` = `custom_field_values`.`custom_field_id` where `custom_field_values`.`customizable_id` = 1 and `custom_field_values`.`customizable_id` is not null and `custom_field_values`.`customizable_type` = 'App\Models\User'
select * from `media` where `media`.`model_id` = 1 and `media`.`model_id` is not null and `media`.`model_type` = 'App\Models\User'

select `value`, `view`, `name` from `custom_field_values` inner join `custom_fields` on `custom_fields`.`id` = `custom_field_values`.`custom_field_id` where `custom_field_values`.`customizable_id` = 1 and `custom_field_values`.`customizable_id` is not null and `custom_field_values`.`customizable_type` = 'App\Models\User'
